* Metamodels

Metamodels *define* a modelling language - Models are not necessarily diagrams.

Example - defining state machines diagram:

[[/home/phil-gab99/Documents/Notes/IFT-6755/20220112222519-metamodels_semantics.org_20220112_222740_0JIuF6.png]]

Example - defining state machine language:

[[/home/phil-gab99/Documents/Notes/IFT-6755/20220112222519-metamodels_semantics.org_20220112_224106_rhPoiy.png]]

- Given a metamodel, we can instantiate a simple state machine

In the world of meta-modelling, we talk about *meta-layers*
- Allows the description of the instanciatiion relationship between models

[[/home/phil-gab99/Documents/Notes/IFT-6755/20220112222519-metamodels_semantics.org_20220112_223203_TZdJgD.png]]  

- Layer M0 describes the real world objects
- Layer M1 describes the  high-level model of the the particular real world object of interest
  - To differentiate between the instance of a video in the real-world and the model, we talk instead about a *snapshot*.
- Layer M2 describes the M1 model, it is a meta-model
  - At this level, instances are given a classifier via another object-type class
- Layer M3 describes the M2 meta-model, it is a meta-meta-model
  - Language that allows definition of meta-models - API that allows for defining other models

** Semantics

What does the model mean?
The semantics of a state machine could be defined as the set of all the traces that it allows.

[[/home/phil-gab99/Documents/Notes/IFT-6755/20220112222519-metamodels_semantics.org_20220112_224609_IKBBZL.png]]

The same approach can be used to define a meta-model.
- A meta-model is just another model, a model for describing models.
- The semantics of a meta-model is the set of all instance models that can be instanciated from this meta-model
- This means that semantics can be defined for all sorts of meta-layers

  [[/home/phil-gab99/Documents/Notes/IFT-6755/20220112222519-metamodels_semantics.org_20220112_224815_JWtjHb.png]]

  Semantics can be though of as sets:

  [[/home/phil-gab99/Documents/Notes/IFT-6755/20220112222519-metamodels_semantics.org_20220112_225146_XrtwUs.png]]
